model_explanation: if Sam only gave Ellen bananas, then giving bananas to Rob contradicts that exclusivity.
if Sam only gave Rob grapes, giving Rob oranges contradicts the exclusivity implied by "only."
if Sam only gave Tom apples, giving apples to Bill contradicts the exclusivity of giving apples only to Tom.
if Sam only gave Mary apples, giving Mary bananas contradicts the exclusivity of giving her only apples.
if Sam only gave Ellen oranges, giving oranges to Sue contradicts that exclusivity.
giving Rob only oranges entails that Sam didn’t give Rob apples or anything else.
the statement about giving Bill bananas does not necessarily imply anything about Ellen, making them independent.
the statement about giving Rob bananas does not imply or contradict giving bananas to Sue— they could have separate contexts.
while Bill getting bananas excludes others getting them in that strict context, it does not directly entail anything about Mary in a broader context.
giving grapes only to Ellen suggests no others got grapes, but this broad contextual reading still doesn’t fully entail a specific statement about Rob. It’s independent.
